abstract: President Donald Trump on Saturday criticized House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi for holding off on sending the articles of impeachment against him to the Senate.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Saturday criticized House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi for holding off on sending the articles of impeachment against him to the Senate.
lead_paragraph: WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump on Saturday criticized House of Representatives Speaker Nancy Pelosi for holding off on sending the articles of impeachment against him to the Senate.
headline_main: Trump Slams House's Impeachment Delay as 'So Unfair'
headline_print_headline: Trump Slams House's Impeachment Delay as 'So Unfair'

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg encountered tough questions and some skepticism about how he'd help end racial disparities in policing as he worked to reach out to Nevada's communities of color Saturday.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg encountered tough questions and some skepticism about how he'd help end racial disparities in policing as he worked to reach out to Nevada's communities of color Saturday.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Democratic presidential candidate Pete Buttigieg tackled issues of racial disparity as he met with Nevada's communities of color Saturday, though the small-town Indiana mayor encountered tough questions and skepticism from some voters.
headline_main: Buttigieg Playing Catchup in Reaching Nevada Voters of Color
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Playing Catchup in Reaching Nevada Voters of Color

abstract: The closing passage in  President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter  to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
snippet: The closing passage in  President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter  to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The closing passage in President Donald Trump's impeachment-eve letter to House Speaker Nancy Pelosi had the ring of truth to it. He was writing his thoughts for history, he said. For 100 years from now, "when people look back at this affair.”
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Distorted Letter to Dems and History
headline_print_headline: AP FACT CHECK: Trump's Distorted Letter to Dems and History

abstract: President Donald Trump is in sunny Florida after his historic impeachment, while plans for his speedy trial back in Washington remained clouded. Senate leaders jockeying for leverage have failed to agree on procedures for the trial.
snippet: President Donald Trump is in sunny Florida after his historic impeachment, while plans for his speedy trial back in Washington remained clouded. Senate leaders jockeying for leverage have failed to agree on procedures for the trial.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump is in sunny Florida after his historic impeachment, while plans for his speedy trial back in Washington remained clouded. Senate leaders jockeying for leverage have failed to agree on procedures for the trial.
headline_main: Plans for Impeachment Trial Get Foggy Before Holiday Break
headline_print_headline: Plans for Impeachment Trial Get Foggy Before Holiday Break

abstract: The financial sector, blamed by progressives for spawning the 2008 economic collapse, is lining up behind Pete Buttigieg’s presidential campaign.
snippet: The financial sector, blamed by progressives for spawning the 2008 economic collapse, is lining up behind Pete Buttigieg’s presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The financial sector, blamed by progressives for spawning the 2008 economic collapse, is lining up behind Pete Buttigieg’s presidential campaign.
headline_main: Buttigieg Leads 2020 Rivals in Wall Street Contributions
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Leads 2020 Rivals in Wall Street Contributions

abstract: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — As Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar escalated their attacks on Pete Buttigieg in Thursday night’s Democratic debate, and Mr. Buttigieg forcefully pushed back, a crucial if unspoken fact was driving the political combat: All three candidates are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.

abstract: President Donald Trump escaped the chill of Washington and his impeachment on Friday to celebrate Christmas and New Year's in sunny Florida with family and friends.
snippet: President Donald Trump escaped the chill of Washington and his impeachment on Friday to celebrate Christmas and New Year's in sunny Florida with family and friends.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump escaped the chill of Washington and his impeachment on Friday to celebrate Christmas and New Year's in sunny Florida with family and friends.
headline_main: Trump Escapes Chill of Washington for Florida Holiday
headline_print_headline: Trump Escapes Chill of Washington for Florida Holiday

abstract: Joe Biden has been fighting a stutter since childhood, and he said Friday he has no regrets about talking openly about it after one of his responses in Thursday's presidential debate prompted a mocking tweet from former White House press secretary Sarah Sanders.
snippet: Joe Biden has been fighting a stutter since childhood, and he said Friday he has no regrets about talking openly about it after one of his responses in Thursday's presidential debate prompted a mocking tweet from former White House press secretary...
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Joe Biden has been fighting a stutter since childhood, and he said Friday he has no regrets about talking openly about it after one of his responses in Thursday's presidential debate prompted a mocking tweet from former White House press secretary Sarah Sanders.
headline_main: Biden: No Regrets for Talking Openly About Stuttering
headline_print_headline: Biden: No Regrets for Talking Openly About Stuttering

abstract: In the final question of Thursday's Democratic presidential debate, the seven candidates were asked whether they would rather give a gift to someone on the stage. Or, they could ask for forgiveness.
